#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.219"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.219:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.219:0.2"
msgid "21. Karajakāyavagga "
msgstr "21. The Body Born of Deeds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.219:0.3"
msgid "219. Karajakāyasutta "
msgstr "219. The Body Born of Deeds "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.219:1.1"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi, "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced. "

msgctxt "an10.219:1.2"
msgid "tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye. "
msgstr "And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period. "

msgctxt "an10.219:1.3"
msgid "Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: catutthaṃ → catutthiṃ (?)
msgctxt "an10.219:2.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ vigatābhijjho vigatabyāpādo asammūḷho sampajāno paṭissato mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "That noble disciple is rid of desire, rid of ill will, unconfused, aware, and mindful. They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.300, sc3
msgctxt "an10.219:3.1"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "an10.219:3.2"
msgid "‘pubbe kho me idaṃ cittaṃ parittaṃ ahosi abhāvitaṃ, etarahi pana me idaṃ cittaṃ appamāṇaṃ subhāvitaṃ. Yaṃ kho pana kiñci pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ, na taṃ tatrāvasissati na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Formerly my mind was limited and undeveloped. Now it’s limitless and well developed. Whatever limited deeds I’ve done don’t remain or persist there.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.219:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

#. VAR: ayaṃ → ce ayaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: api nu kho → api nu so (?)
msgctxt "an10.219:4.2"
msgid "daharatagge ce so ayaṃ kumāro mettaṃ cetovimuttiṃ bhāveyya, api nu kho pāpakammaṃ kareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Suppose a child had developed the heart’s release by love from their childhood on. Would they still do any bad deed?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.219:4.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an10.219:5.1"
msgid "“Akarontaṃ kho pana pāpakammaṃ api nu kho dukkhaṃ phuseyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Not doing any bad deed, would they still experience any suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.219:5.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“No, sir. "

msgctxt "an10.219:5.3"
msgid "Akarontañhi, bhante, pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī”ti. "
msgstr "For if they don’t do any bad deed, from where would suffering afflict them?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an10.219:6.1"
msgid "“Bhāvetabbā kho panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, mettācetovimutti itthiyā vā purisena vā. "
msgstr "“This heart’s release by love should be developed by women or men. "

msgctxt "an10.219:6.2"
msgid "Itthiyā vā, bhikkhave, purisassa vā nāyaṃ kāyo ādāya gamanīyo. "
msgstr "For neither women nor men take this body with them when they go. "

msgctxt "an10.219:6.3"
msgid "Cittantaro ayaṃ, bhikkhave, macco. "
msgstr "The mind is what’s inside mortal beings. "

msgctxt "an10.219:6.4"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "an10.219:6.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho me idaṃ kiñci pubbe iminā karajakāyena pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, sabbaṃ taṃ idha vedanīyaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Whatever bad deeds I have done in the past with this deed-born body I will experience here. "

msgctxt "an10.219:6.6"
msgid "na taṃ anugaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "It will not follow me to my next life.’ "

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.219:6.7"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, mettā cetovimutti anāgāmitāya saṃvattati, idha paññassa bhikkhuno uttari vimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato. "
msgstr "The heart’s release by love developed in this way leads to non-return for a wise mendicant here who has not penetrated to a higher freedom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an10.219:7.1"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion … "

msgctxt "an10.219:7.2"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing … "

msgctxt "an10.219:7.3"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. "

msgctxt "an10.219:7.4"
msgid "Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.301, sc8
msgctxt "an10.219:8.1"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "an10.219:8.2"
msgid "‘pubbe kho me idaṃ cittaṃ parittaṃ ahosi abhāvitaṃ, etarahi pana me idaṃ cittaṃ appamāṇaṃ subhāvitaṃ. Yaṃ kho pana kiñci pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ, na taṃ tatrāvasissati na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Formerly my mind was limited and undeveloped. Now it’s limitless and well developed. Whatever limited deeds I’ve done don’t remain or persist there.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an10.219:9.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "an10.219:9.2"
msgid "daharatagge ce so ayaṃ kumāro upekkhaṃ cetovimuttiṃ bhāveyya, api nu kho pāpakammaṃ kareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Suppose a child had developed the heart’s release by equanimity from their childhood on. Would they still do any bad deed?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.219:9.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
